caption: David and Dad’s is absolutely the best restaurant, café, food place in the entire city of Baltimore Maryland. The staff is unbelievable, and the food is “out of this world”. The portions you receive are large enough for two meals, but the pricing is very reasonable. I wish I would’ve found this cafe sooner, and I also wish they were open on weekends which presently they are not. It’s a definite must try if you’re in Baltimore. It’s a shame you can’t give them six stars.
This place is amazing. Great breakfast food. The coffee cake is the best I’ve ever had.
I go there at least once or twice a week. They have delicious breakfast and the staff really takes the time to get to know each customer. All around great Cafe, sometimes I even study there as well.
Great coffee, great food, great people

Great food at great prices with Great customer service, They have breakfast  lunch, smoothies. Vegan, vegetarian and  Pescatarian options!!! Smoothies,Salads,Sandwiches,Breakfast, and so much more, pies, cookies, soup, the menu is AMAZING!! They have everyday specials Everything is baked, grilled, prepared fresh daily. They have a dine in area and a bar !!!!! They open at 6am so if you live near you can get breakfast before work and lunch after its that great. If you haven't tried it you should😋

Excellent surprise for breakfast while in Baltimore. Very nice conversion of an apparent bank, which lended to the atmosphere. Plenty of menu items, sizeable portions, fresh ingredients, and when our breakfasts arrived, the taste was absolutely perfect!  Definitely rates a return trip!

The food was great. The people that worked here were friendly and helpful. The coffee was quite refreshing.

This place was amazing! This is my first time in Baltimore and I was just searching for somewhere near my hotel for breakfast. As I walked in I was greeted with the wonderful smells from the kitchen and a very unique entrance way that is fitting to the area of Baltimore. The staff were all incredibly kind and patient as I browsed the menu, readily answering any questions I had and making recommendations. Prices were very much so on the affordable side and after ordering enough food for 4 peoples, with a couple drinks and smoothies it still only took about 40$ from my pocket. All in all I will definitely be sure to visit this place everytime I am in town, they have earned a lifelong customer!

If you happen to be in the neighborhood and need a quick casual breakfast or lunch, go here. V. nice selection on the menu. Very helpful staff. We couldn't get into via the front door because of steps and because one of us was handicapped. So they let us in via a "back" door, a delivery entrance that one of the staff had to go to to open for us. Went through a maze of hallways, to an elevator, and got into the restaurant. Very worthwhile. We were there for breakfast. Try the D&D Breakfast Bowl. And try the peppermint hot chocolate. Both excellent. We viewed the lunch and the dinner menu and wished that the previous night instead of going to the B&O American restaurant at the Kimpton Hotel, we had gone here. Tastier food for a much better price. You place your order, get a number, and they bring the food to your table. You pay after you eat. Honor system for getting your drinks. Lots of background activity preparing food deliveries, probably for holiday parties, so you know this is a popular place. We are out-of-towners and feel we lucked into this for breakfast.

Love the cream of crab soup. How is there so much crab in it? Great biscuits. I wish they had a better Caesar dressing not everyone likes vinaigrette-type dressings. Also, sometimes the soup choices are sad compared to what they could be. No complaints otherwise. Thanks!

The fries are also very yummy and the service was outstanding.  The place was clean and busy specially during lunch I'll be going back for th e breaskfast bowl my coworkers rave about them. The chocolate chip pancakes didn’t taste like it was fully done; in fact it tasted like it was from the freezer and the outer parts of the pancakes were still cold. Disgusting! When that wasn’t working out, I went to the coffee for a relief but it tasted bitter and there were solid bits in my mouth as I drank it! I instantly spit the coffee out on my pancakes and threw it all away. Highly disappointed in my “breakfast”. A waste of $13!!! I would’ve went back for a refund or SOMETHING but it’s too cold! Ugh! 😡🤬

Wow! Am I ever glad I found this place!  On the hunt for breakfast, as the hotel I'm staying at offers a very limited breakfast, I decided to try Dave and Dad's right around the corner. Even another patron passing by asked what it was that I ordered.  I'll even dare to say, that it was the best omelet that I ever had!   The home fries were very good too, requiring no condiments to spruce them up.  Excellent coffee as well.  I'm in town a few more days, and I will definitely be coming back.  My only regret is that I didn't take a photo of that magnificent omelet! LOL!

Cool building, boring food.  I have gotten a few of the sandwiches here and they are pretty bland. This would be fine based on price if it didn't take so much time to get my food each time.  I can understand liking this place if you become a regular because they seem to remember people and treat regulars well. I have seen multiple employees interact with customers when they have an issue with the food and they always seem respectful and quickly try and make it right for the customer. This dedication to regulars is great.  The problem is for those who are not regulars.  While I'm sure any problems with food would be addressed quickly and respectfully, the amount of time non regulars need to wait for their food is excessive. When you are waiting for your food and watch customer after customer come in to order and get their orders expedited once someone in the back recognizes them, it gets pretty annoying.  I have watched multiple people come in, order the exact same thing as me and when they go over to the pickup counter, they are recognized and asked what they ordered and their order is then rushed through while I sit there twiddling my thumbs. If the food was particularly good, this would only be a minor annoyance but why should I invest the effort to become a regular in order to just get food in a reasonable amount of time when it is only passable?
